1 shall appoint six members in accordance with G.S. 120-121, three at the recommendation of the
2 Speaker of the House of Representatives and three at the recommendation of the President Pro
3 Tempore of the Senate, to succeed two members of the Council appointed by the Governor to
4 represent the General Assembly whose terms expire December 31, 2026, and four at-large
5 members appointed by the Governor whose terms expire on December 31, 2026; the General
6 Assembly shall appoint two members in accordance with G.S. 120-121, one at the
7 recommendation of the Speaker of the House of Representatives and one at the recommendation
8 of the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, to succeed two at-large members appointed by the
9 Governor whose terms expire on December 31, 2027; and the General Assembly shall appoint
10 four members in accordance with G.S. 120-121, two at the recommendation of the Speaker of
11 the House of Representatives and two at the recommendation of the President Pro Tempore of
12 the Senate, to succeed four members appointed by the Governor whose terms expire on
13 December 31, 2028. Members appointed to the Council by the General Assembly pursuant to
14 this subsection shall serve for a term of three years.
15
16 PART IV. REPEAL OF RURAL HEALTH CARE STABILIZATION PROGRAM
17 SECTION 4.1. Article 2 of Chapter 131A of the General Statutes, with the exception
18 of G.S. 131A-32, as recodified and amended by Part I of this act, is repealed.
19
20 PART V. TRANSFERS AND APPROPRIATIONS
21 SECTION 5.1. Effective July 1, 2026, the entire unrestricted cash balance of the
22 Rural Health Care Stabilization Fund within the Office of State Budget and Management (Budget
23 Code 23018) is transferred to the Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund created by G.S. 131E-74,
24 as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of this act. The funds transferred are appropriated for the fiscal year
25 in which they are transferred. Any remaining principal and interest payments due to the Rural
26 Health Care Stabilization Fund on or after July 1, 2026, shall be paid to the Rural Healthcare
27 Infrastructure Fund.
28 SECTION 5.2. Notwithstanding G.S. 131E-74(c), as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of
29 this act, there is appropriated from the Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund to the Department
30 of Health and Human Services, Division of Central Management and Support, Office of Rural
31 Health, the sum of one million dollars ($1,000,000) in nonrecurring funds to fund a contract with
32 Rural Healthcare Initiative, Inc., a nonprofit organization, to continue the work funded by S.L.
33 2023-134 involving the creation of effective models of sustainable healthcare for North Carolina
34 rural communities; to develop cost estimates for achieving the healthcare facilities described in
35 these initial models of sustainable healthcare; and to support the work of the North Carolina State
36 Health Coordinating Council and the Office of Rural Health in developing a plan for the
37 establishment and administration of a Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Program funded by the
38 Rural Healthcare Infrastructure Fund created by G.S. 131E-74, as enacted by Section 1.1(b) of
39 this act.
40
41 PART VI. EFFECTIVE DATE
42 SECTION 6.1. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective July 1, 2026.
